WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.695 --> 00:00:14.080
Your mom sent us something from D.C.

2
00:00:14.716 --> 00:00:16.002
Oh. that's right.

3
00:00:16.004 --> 00:00:17.918
She mentioned something
on the phone the other day.

4
00:00:17.919 --> 00:00:19.104
She said it's a surprise

5
00:00:19.105 --> 00:00:20.921
that'll come in handy for
the little bun in the oven.

6
00:00:20.922 --> 00:00:22.923
Maybe it's another tutu

7
00:00:22.924 --> 00:00:25.192
to go with the ten others
she's given us.

8
00:00:25.193 --> 00:00:27.981
Baby. what can I tell you?
That woman loves her some QVC.

9
00:00:27.982 --> 00:00:29.722
With our baby girl on the way.

10
00:00:29.723 --> 00:00:31.803
that remote control is
pretty much glued to her hand.

11
00:00:32.813 --> 00:00:34.858
Charice enjoying her sister's house?

12
00:00:34.859 --> 00:00:38.426
All those two ever do is eat.
shop and eat some more.

13
00:00:38.427 --> 00:00:39.907
She's in heaven.

14
00:00:40.342 --> 00:00:41.821
Wow.

15
00:00:41.822 --> 00:00:43.649
Huh.

16
00:00:43.650 --> 00:00:45.869
Doesn't look like anything QVC sells.

17
00:00:45.870 --> 00:00:49.508
Wow. that's Winnie's
old christening gown.

18
00:00:51.675 --> 00:00:53.746
My granny made this by hand.

19
00:00:53.747 --> 00:00:56.619
And then after Winnie.
three more of my cousins wore it. so...

20
00:00:56.620 --> 00:01:00.274
- kind of became a family heirloom.
- Aw.

21
00:01:00.275 --> 00:01:01.711
It's beautiful.

22
00:01:01.712 --> 00:01:03.713
Just don't know what we're
supposed to do with it.

23
00:01:03.714 --> 00:01:05.323
What do you mean?

24
00:01:05.324 --> 00:01:07.524
You got something else in mind
for our daughter to wear?

25
00:01:08.633 --> 00:01:10.068
To wear for what?

26
00:01:10.550 --> 00:01:11.896
Her baptism?

27
00:01:12.842 --> 00:01:15.376
Since when are we planning to
baptize our daughter?

28
00:01:15.377 --> 00:01:17.335
I asked Luca to be our godfather.

29
00:01:17.336 --> 00:01:18.815
- You signed off on it.
- Yeah...

30
00:01:18.816 --> 00:01:21.338
I didn't think you meant
that in a churchgoing sense.

31
00:01:21.339 --> 00:01:23.429
How else did you think I meant it?

32
00:01:23.717 --> 00:01:26.300
You know. like. Luca giving his godchild

33
00:01:26.301 --> 00:01:27.867
an extra 20 bucks on her birthday.

34
00:01:27.868 --> 00:01:30.261
or taking her to her first Dodger game.

35
00:01:30.262 --> 00:01:32.149
Okay. Nichelle. I know you're
not all that religious. but...

36
00:01:32.150 --> 00:01:33.481
Well. neither are you.

37
00:01:33.482 --> 00:01:34.918
Come on. when's the last time

38
00:01:34.919 --> 00:01:37.138
you picked up a Bible or went to church?

39
00:01:37.733 --> 00:01:38.835
Okay. but that doesn't mean

40
00:01:38.836 --> 00:01:40.881
I don't want our daughter
to have a christening.

41
00:01:41.912 --> 00:01:43.841
Well. this is news to me.

42
00:01:44.624 --> 00:01:47.974
Religion was shoved down
my throat as a kid.

43
00:01:47.975 --> 00:01:51.325
I'm grown now and I don't
necessarily subscribe

44
00:01:51.326 --> 00:01:52.544
to what the church says

45
00:01:52.545 --> 00:01:54.764
I should or shouldn't do. especially

46
00:01:54.765 --> 00:01:56.809
when it comes to raising our child.

47
00:01:59.552 --> 00:02:01.335
I know. duty calls.

48
00:02:01.336 --> 00:02:03.817
- Go. be safe.
- Baby. I'm sorry.

49
00:02:06.167 --> 00:02:09.078
- Can we talk more about this later?
- We can...

50
00:02:09.079 --> 00:02:11.694
but it took me a long time to figure out

51
00:02:11.695 --> 00:02:12.999
my own beliefs.

52
00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:16.351
I'm not gonna change my mind now.

53
00:02:18.484 --> 00:02:19.833
Bye.

54
00:02:33.003 --> 00:02:35.505
Got a female suspect. goes by Abby.

55
00:02:35.506 --> 00:02:38.181
Armed and barricaded inside
with seven hostages. all staff.

56
00:02:38.182 --> 00:02:39.573
Is she a resident of the shelter?

57
00:02:39.574 --> 00:02:40.835
She's living here with her son.

58
00:02:40.836 --> 00:02:42.576
Never caused any trouble before today.

59
00:02:42.577 --> 00:02:44.752
Homeless shelter's not exactly
immune to mental health issues.

60
00:02:44.753 --> 00:02:46.459
Any idea what set her off?

61
00:02:46.460 --> 00:02:48.254
Claims that her child went
missing last night.

62
00:02:48.255 --> 00:02:50.015
Thinks the staff had
something to do with it.

63
00:02:50.250 --> 00:02:53.178
Seven hostages at gunpoint.
She is desperate right now.

64
00:02:53.179 --> 00:02:54.440
Let's end this.

65
00:02:54.441 --> 00:02:55.746
Tan. Street. you got the one side.

66
00:02:55.747 --> 00:02:56.728
Deacon. with me on the three side.

67
00:02:56.729 --> 00:02:58.184
Roger that.

68
00:03:04.234 --> 00:03:05.974
20-David. we're in.

69
00:03:05.975 --> 00:03:07.890
Roger. Making entry.

70
00:03:17.377 --> 00:03:20.252
LAPD! Hands where I can see them.

71
00:03:20.253 --> 00:03:21.813
Turn around. walk backwards towards me.

72
00:03:23.427 --> 00:03:25.239
All right. put your hands down.

73
00:03:25.240 --> 00:03:26.951
- What's your name?
- I-I'm sorry. My name's Ruth.

74
00:03:26.952 --> 00:03:28.619
I-I live here.

75
00:03:28.620 --> 00:03:29.911
I was hiding 'cause I was scared.

76
00:03:29.912 --> 00:03:31.434
You know the woman with the gun?

77
00:03:31.435 --> 00:03:34.132
Abby? Yeah. Micah's her little boy.

78
00:03:34.133 --> 00:03:35.699
She's nice.

79
00:03:35.700 --> 00:03:37.820
She let me borrow her blazer
for a job interview once.

80
00:03:38.370 --> 00:03:40.907
26-David. we have one resident.
physically unharmed.

81
00:03:40.908 --> 00:03:42.561
The missing son's name is Micah.

82
00:03:42.562 --> 00:03:44.520
Roger. Approaching east side
of the building

83
00:03:44.521 --> 00:03:45.957
toward the bunk room.

84
00:03:51.362 --> 00:03:53.059
Snake cam in.

85
00:03:54.429 --> 00:03:56.518
The door's partially obstructed.

86
00:03:57.186 --> 00:03:59.274
Look. this'll all be over

87
00:03:59.275 --> 00:04:01.182
if you just tell me
what you did with Micah.

88
00:04:01.183 --> 00:04:03.669
Abby. we already said.
we don't know where he is.

89
00:04:03.670 --> 00:04:05.497
Stop lying and tell me!

90
00:04:05.498 --> 00:04:06.698
I'm not lying.

91
00:04:07.344 --> 00:04:09.414
Damn it! Where is he?

92
00:04:09.415 --> 00:04:11.851
I've got visual on
our suspect and hostages.

93
00:04:11.852 --> 00:04:13.026
Far left. corner of the room.

94
00:04:13.027 --> 00:04:14.750
There's enough space for a flashbang.

95
00:04:21.471 --> 00:04:22.671
Ah!

96
00:04:27.290 --> 00:04:28.792
LAPD!

97
00:04:30.208 --> 00:04:32.090
Come on. let's get out of here.
Stay low.

98
00:04:33.500 --> 00:04:35.268
That's it. Move. move. move. Stay down.

99
00:04:35.508 --> 00:04:36.702
Come on. with me.

100
00:04:36.703 --> 00:04:38.139
Abby...

101
00:04:39.097 --> 00:04:42.187
My name is Hondo. I'm with
the LAPD. Can you hear me?

102
00:04:43.208 --> 00:04:44.929
If you can hear me. answer me. Abby.

103
00:04:45.375 --> 00:04:47.191
I already told the other cop.

104
00:04:47.192 --> 00:04:50.543
I am not moving until you get me my son.

105
00:04:50.917 --> 00:04:53.241
All right. then we're both
on the same page.

106
00:04:53.242 --> 00:04:54.938
We want to help you find your son.

107
00:04:54.939 --> 00:04:57.332
Well. if that were true.
then he'd be here.

108
00:04:57.333 --> 00:04:59.986
I mean. all of you...
you just. you just lie.

109
00:04:59.987 --> 00:05:02.119
Like. none of you give
a damn about me or Micah!

110
00:05:02.120 --> 00:05:03.599
No. that may be true about them.

111
00:05:03.600 --> 00:05:05.949
but you and me.
we don't know each other. Abby.

112
00:05:05.950 --> 00:05:08.250
We got ourselves
a clean slate. all right?

113
00:05:09.083 --> 00:05:10.998
I'm gonna start by being
real honest with you.

114
00:05:11.260 --> 00:05:13.155
You put yourself in
one hell of a situation

115
00:05:13.156 --> 00:05:14.679
with all these hostages and cops.

116
00:05:15.083 --> 00:05:17.309
There's a lot of people here
on account of you

117
00:05:17.583 --> 00:05:20.355
when the person this is
really about isn't here. Abby.

118
00:05:20.356 --> 00:05:21.792
No.

119
00:05:22.375 --> 00:05:23.625
How old is Micah?

120
00:05:25.917 --> 00:05:27.117
Eight.

121
00:05:27.625 --> 00:05:29.974
An eight-year-old boy
out there without his mother...

122
00:05:30.292 --> 00:05:31.931
Abby. the longer you let this go on.

123
00:05:31.932 --> 00:05:33.803
- the less likely we'll find him.
- No...

124
00:05:33.804 --> 00:05:37.764
Every minute is crucial.
and we need you to help us.

125
00:05:38.997 --> 00:05:40.113
Abby. that's the only way

126
00:05:40.114 --> 00:05:42.208
we're gonna be able to
bring Micah back to you.

127
00:05:45.119 --> 00:05:47.339
Come on now. put the gun
down on the ground.

128
00:05:47.709 --> 00:05:50.450
Show me your hands
and come out to me slowly.

129
00:05:51.542 --> 00:05:53.839
All right. Turn around.

130
00:05:53.840 --> 00:05:55.434
Walk towards my voice.

131
00:05:57.542 --> 00:05:59.003
Going hands-on.

132
00:06:01.048 --> 00:06:02.614
Look. I don't. I don't care

133
00:06:02.615 --> 00:06:03.963
what happens to me. okay?

134
00:06:03.964 --> 00:06:06.793
Just bring me back my baby. Please.

135
00:06:12.708 --> 00:06:13.908
Hondo.

136
00:06:14.801 --> 00:06:16.802
You guys should see this.

137
00:06:16.803 --> 00:06:18.238
The business next door pulled this

138
00:06:18.239 --> 00:06:19.805
from one of their security cameras.

139
00:06:19.806 --> 00:06:22.154
It's from 2:00 a.m. this morning.
The alley behind their store.

140
00:06:22.155 --> 00:06:23.722
- Is that Micah?
- Yup.

141
00:06:23.723 --> 00:06:26.123
The man with him works here
at the shelter. He's the janitor.

142
00:06:26.124 --> 00:06:27.381
Judging by the way they move.

143
00:06:27.382 --> 00:06:29.102
that guy did not want to be seen
leaving with the kid.

144
00:06:29.103 --> 00:06:30.654
I don't want to think about
what this guy wants

145
00:06:30.655 --> 00:06:31.861
with an eight-year-old child.

146
00:06:31.862 --> 00:06:33.194
I'm gonna go with nothing good.

147
00:06:33.195 --> 00:06:35.866
We better find that boy and
find him fast. before it's too late.

148
00:07:12.865 --> 00:07:15.152
What do we have on the creep
who abducted Micah?

149
00:07:15.154 --> 00:07:16.728
Looks like our janitor was working

150
00:07:16.729 --> 00:07:18.077
at the homeless shelter under a fake ID.

151
00:07:18.078 --> 00:07:19.775
calling himself Tony Cruz.

152
00:07:19.776 --> 00:07:21.602
The name didn't yield
any background info.

153
00:07:21.603 --> 00:07:23.691
so we pulled his prints and found this.

154
00:07:23.692 --> 00:07:25.824
His real name is Liam Dunn.

155
00:07:25.825 --> 00:07:27.870
Mr. Dunn here was just released
from prison six months ago.

156
00:07:27.871 --> 00:07:29.481
What was he in for?

157
00:07:29.482 --> 00:07:31.612
Did five years.
and change up in Corcoran

158
00:07:31.613 --> 00:07:33.136
for assaulting an officer
at a traffic stop.

159
00:07:33.137 --> 00:07:34.441
Before that.

160
00:07:34.442 --> 00:07:36.356
string of bar fights. a couple of DUIs.

161
00:07:36.357 --> 00:07:38.489
- Your textbook hothead.
- Yeah. but get this...

162
00:07:38.490 --> 00:07:40.186
His rap sheet only spans back

163
00:07:40.187 --> 00:07:41.709
a year and a half
prior to his last arrest.

164
00:07:41.710 --> 00:07:43.473
Before that. no trouble with the law.

165
00:07:43.474 --> 00:07:44.849
not even a parking ticket.

166
00:07:44.850 --> 00:07:47.150
So the guy goes most of his
life as a model citizen.

167
00:07:47.151 --> 00:07:48.367
then suddenly spirals out of control?

168
00:07:48.368 --> 00:07:49.935
Wonder what triggered him.

169
00:07:49.936 --> 00:07:51.155
Anything there hint towards motive?

170
00:07:51.156 --> 00:07:53.678
Not yet. Commander. But our
kidnapper is fresh out of prison.

171
00:07:53.679 --> 00:07:56.550
- Did five years for assaulting a cop.
- Felon. Wonderful.

172
00:07:56.551 --> 00:07:58.814
- Any history of sex crimes?
- None.

173
00:07:58.815 --> 00:08:00.641
Yeah. but you'd think.
if this was trafficking.

174
00:08:00.642 --> 00:08:02.689
- there'd be something in his rap sheet.
- Maybe. maybe not.

175
00:08:02.690 --> 00:08:05.331
Either way. we got
a 51-year-old ex-convict

176
00:08:05.332 --> 00:08:06.810
who took an eight-year-old boy.

177
00:08:06.811 --> 00:08:08.899
The shelter's housing
supervisor wasn't there earlier.

178
00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:11.059
So we'll go back. try to get
more intel on the janitor.

179
00:08:11.060 --> 00:08:14.059
Go get a lead on this
son of a bitch. and get it fast!

180
00:08:18.073 --> 00:08:20.249
Did you hear anything about my baby?

181
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:22.164
I mean. I've been waiting
here. and-and nothing.

182
00:08:22.165 --> 00:08:23.817
You know. not a word. from any of you.

183
00:08:23.818 --> 00:08:25.993
Abby. just take a seat.
We got you some water.

184
00:08:25.994 --> 00:08:27.560
No. but you're not hearing me.

185
00:08:27.561 --> 00:08:29.652
We got to find him before it's too late.
Please!

186
00:08:29.653 --> 00:08:30.823
And we're doing everything in our power

187
00:08:30.824 --> 00:08:32.652
to do just that. But in the meantime.

188
00:08:32.653 --> 00:08:34.749
I'd like you to sit down
and answer some questions.

189
00:08:34.750 --> 00:08:36.187
Do you understand?

190
00:08:38.808 --> 00:08:40.183
I know what this looks like.

191
00:08:40.642 --> 00:08:43.913
I mean. what kind of mother leaves
her child at a homeless shelter.

192
00:08:43.914 --> 00:08:45.883
- right?
- Is that what you did?

193
00:08:45.884 --> 00:08:47.580
You left Micah there
without supervision?

194
00:08:47.581 --> 00:08:50.017
Well. that's the thing. I didn't.

195
00:08:50.018 --> 00:08:51.062
Honest to God.

196
00:08:51.063 --> 00:08:52.759
Okay. well. then why don't you try to

197
00:08:52.760 --> 00:08:54.501
explain to us how this all happened?

198
00:08:55.629 --> 00:08:57.503
So I work at a.

199
00:08:57.504 --> 00:08:59.288
I work at a gas station up on Olympic.

200
00:08:59.289 --> 00:09:02.029
And my boss is like a real piece. right?

201
00:09:02.030 --> 00:09:04.448
He-he switched the schedule on me.

202
00:09:04.449 --> 00:09:06.208
and he forced me to work graveyard.

203
00:09:06.209 --> 00:09:07.557
And. like. I need this job.

204
00:09:07.558 --> 00:09:09.167
You know? And so the people
at the shelter said

205
00:09:09.168 --> 00:09:11.174
they'd look after him
and I trusted them.

206
00:09:11.175 --> 00:09:12.725
The people at the shelter.

207
00:09:13.892 --> 00:09:15.092
Right.

208
00:09:15.392 --> 00:09:17.314
What time did your
shift start last night?

209
00:09:17.315 --> 00:09:18.369
Uh...

210
00:09:18.370 --> 00:09:21.440
I started work at like 1:00.
and then Micah's school

211
00:09:21.441 --> 00:09:23.050
called me at like 9:00 in the morning

212
00:09:23.051 --> 00:09:25.227
and they said that he never showed up.

213
00:09:25.228 --> 00:09:27.751
so I ran back to the shelter
and he was gone.

214
00:09:27.752 --> 00:09:30.839
I mean. I thought the staff was lying.

215
00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:33.931
You know? I thought they had.
like. reported me to DCFS

216
00:09:33.932 --> 00:09:37.065
- for. like. neglect or something.
- How long have you been sober?

217
00:09:39.285 --> 00:09:40.459
13 months.

218
00:09:40.460 --> 00:09:41.765
And before that?

219
00:09:41.766 --> 00:09:44.725
Well. before that. it was really bad.

220
00:09:45.557 --> 00:09:48.253
I mean. Micah and I got evicted
from our apartment and...

221
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:51.257
You mean. you got evicted. He's eight.

222
00:09:52.009 --> 00:09:53.991
If you were so strung out on drugs.

223
00:09:53.992 --> 00:09:55.341
why wasn't Micah taken from you?

224
00:09:56.140 --> 00:09:57.958
I got clean before all that.

225
00:09:57.960 --> 00:10:01.441
I've been doing everything I can
to get us back on track.

226
00:10:01.442 --> 00:10:03.401
And you consider your life
to be on track now?

227
00:10:04.285 --> 00:10:06.988
Compared to where we were
a year ago. yeah. I do.

228
00:10:08.810 --> 00:10:11.333
Um. Abby. this is security footage

229
00:10:11.940 --> 00:10:14.554
taken from a business
next door to the shelter.

230
00:10:14.555 --> 00:10:16.774
Timestamp is 2:00 a.m.

231
00:10:16.775 --> 00:10:18.036
Micah.

232
00:10:18.037 --> 00:10:19.733
- Yeah.
- Uh...

233
00:10:19.734 --> 00:10:21.758
That's-that's Tony. That's the janitor.

234
00:10:21.759 --> 00:10:23.299
Right. Well. you know him as Tony.

235
00:10:23.300 --> 00:10:24.999
but his real name is Liam Dunn.

236
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:28.481
And he's the last person
to be seen with your boy.

237
00:10:28.482 --> 00:10:30.744
His real name? Wh... I don't understand.

238
00:10:30.745 --> 00:10:33.357
Liam was recently released from prison.

239
00:10:33.650 --> 00:10:35.227
Prison?

240
00:10:35.228 --> 00:10:36.882
He was always so nice to us.

241
00:10:37.775 --> 00:10:39.710
Why would he do
something like this? I...

242
00:10:39.711 --> 00:10:41.407
It doesn't make any sense.

243
00:10:41.408 --> 00:10:44.368
You ask me. there's a whole lot
of this that doesn't make sense.

244
00:10:52.115 --> 00:10:54.552
Hey. Street. Not so fast.

245
00:10:56.641 --> 00:10:58.358
What was your problem in there?

246
00:10:59.252 --> 00:11:00.383
Seriously?

247
00:11:00.384 --> 00:11:01.907
You're not buying that whole.

248
00:11:02.400 --> 00:11:04.126
"I'm turning over
a new leaf" routine. right?

249
00:11:04.127 --> 00:11:06.084
I mean. she's rehearsed that bit
a hundred times before.

250
00:11:06.085 --> 00:11:07.999
So. where do you think
she was last night?

251
00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:09.741
You think she was out getting a fix?

252
00:11:10.650 --> 00:11:13.700
Who leaves their eight-year-old
child in a homeless shelter

253
00:11:13.701 --> 00:11:16.268
to be looked after
by complete strangers?

254
00:11:16.269 --> 00:11:18.052
Oh. that's right. A junkie.

255
00:11:18.053 --> 00:11:20.707
The same junkie who just
held hostages at gunpoint.

256
00:11:20.708 --> 00:11:22.753
I agree she's not without fault.

257
00:11:22.754 --> 00:11:25.307
But ultimately.
she cooperated with us then.

258
00:11:25.309 --> 00:11:26.526
She's cooperating with us now.

259
00:11:26.527 --> 00:11:28.007
So. what? She just gets a free pass?

260
00:11:28.695 --> 00:11:29.882
Deac.

261
00:11:29.883 --> 00:11:32.141
the truth is. might be Liam

262
00:11:32.142 --> 00:11:34.121
that snatched Micah. but this is on her.

263
00:11:34.122 --> 00:11:35.666
She just wants us to find her son.

264
00:11:35.667 --> 00:11:38.538
And there's a strong possibility
that that doesn't happen.

265
00:11:38.539 --> 00:11:41.890
So in the meantime. watch your tone.

266
00:11:46.765 --> 00:11:48.679
- What's with him?
- I get the sense

267
00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:51.030
that this case is
dredging up some old issues.

268
00:11:51.342 --> 00:11:53.859
- His mother?
- Yeah. I'll keep my eye on him.

269
00:11:54.425 --> 00:11:56.730
- All right.
- We got any new intel on Liam Dunn?

270
00:11:56.731 --> 00:11:59.994
His criminal history has nothing
to do with trafficking or children.

271
00:11:59.995 --> 00:12:01.822
- Well. maybe he was never got caught.
- Yeah. well. maybe.

272
00:12:01.823 --> 00:12:03.650
But I can't shake the feeling
that we're missing something.

273
00:12:03.651 --> 00:12:05.739
Well. right now. he's our only suspect.

274
00:12:05.740 --> 00:12:08.220
- We find him. we find Micah.
- Hey. Deacon?

275
00:12:08.221 --> 00:12:10.180
- Yeah?
- Can I ask you something?

276
00:12:11.175 --> 00:12:12.375
Yeah.

277
00:12:12.467 --> 00:12:14.531
- What's up?
- It's me and Nichelle.

278
00:12:14.532 --> 00:12:16.054
We had this weird conversation earlier

279
00:12:16.055 --> 00:12:18.188
about whether or not
we were gonna baptize our kid.

280
00:12:18.675 --> 00:12:20.406
She wants to and you don't?

281
00:12:20.407 --> 00:12:22.278
Actually. it's the opposite.

282
00:12:22.279 --> 00:12:23.806
She had strong feelings about it.

283
00:12:23.807 --> 00:12:25.839
I mean. I knew she wasn't very
religious. but I just thought

284
00:12:25.840 --> 00:12:27.866
she'd have a "go with the flow"
kind of attitude about it.

285
00:12:27.867 --> 00:12:29.739
but that was definitely not the case.

286
00:12:31.070 --> 00:12:32.244
What?

287
00:12:32.245 --> 00:12:33.463
No. I'm just a little surprised that.

288
00:12:33.464 --> 00:12:34.855
that you'd want to.

289
00:12:34.856 --> 00:12:36.509
I-I know. I understand.

290
00:12:36.510 --> 00:12:38.294
When was the last time
you saw me in a church?

291
00:12:38.295 --> 00:12:39.992
Three years ago. Victoria's baptism.

292
00:12:42.133 --> 00:12:44.082
Why do you want to baptize your child?

293
00:12:44.083 --> 00:12:45.910
I don't know. Deac.

294
00:12:45.911 --> 00:12:47.955
Look. I haven't kept up
with my Christian upbringing

295
00:12:47.956 --> 00:12:48.996
in a minute. but.

296
00:12:48.997 --> 00:12:52.134
you know. I still consider myself
to be spiritual.

297
00:12:52.135 --> 00:12:53.745
But with a baby on the way...

298
00:12:54.383 --> 00:12:56.573
I guess I'm just questioning
things a lot more these days.

299
00:12:56.574 --> 00:12:58.444
That's something every new father does.

300
00:12:58.445 --> 00:13:00.054
But what do I do with Nichelle?

301
00:13:00.055 --> 00:13:01.665
We're on opposite sides of this one.

302
00:13:01.666 --> 00:13:03.449
I mean. I don't even know
that there's a middle ground.

303
00:13:03.450 --> 00:13:04.798
Okay. first. you need to think why

304
00:13:04.799 --> 00:13:06.365
is this baptism so important to you.

305
00:13:06.366 --> 00:13:08.325
And then sit on it. you know?

306
00:13:08.717 --> 00:13:10.282
If it's something
you decide you really want.

307
00:13:10.283 --> 00:13:13.467
it means a lot to you.
just talk to Nichelle.

308
00:13:14.754 --> 00:13:16.383
She might surprise you.

309
00:13:20.741 --> 00:13:22.219
According to the kid's mother.

310
00:13:22.220 --> 00:13:24.222
this Liam Dunn is a pretty decent guy.

311
00:13:24.223 --> 00:13:25.528
which is zero help to us.

312
00:13:25.529 --> 00:13:26.964
You guys learn anything
new at the shelter?

313
00:13:26.965 --> 00:13:28.618
Well. we talked to
the housing supervisor.

314
00:13:28.619 --> 00:13:30.315
At first. she was
a total deer in headlights.

315
00:13:30.316 --> 00:13:32.839
Seems Liam was liked by
everybody. never a problem.

316
00:13:32.840 --> 00:13:35.089
But while we were there.
the supervisor discovered

317
00:13:35.090 --> 00:13:37.278
a stack of motel vouchers
missing from her office.

318
00:13:37.279 --> 00:13:39.977
And how does that trace back to
our oh-so-likable kidnapper?

319
00:13:39.978 --> 00:13:42.719
Janitor's the only other person
with a key to her office.

320
00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:45.591
So there's a good chance this
dude took the boy to a motel.

321
00:13:45.592 --> 00:13:46.972
Yeah. that's not gross at all.

322
00:13:46.973 --> 00:13:49.140
And all these motels accept
the shelter's vouchers?

323
00:13:49.141 --> 00:13:51.205
All right. I want patrol out
to every one of them.

324
00:13:51.206 --> 00:13:52.816
Wait. Hillwinds Inn on Van Ness.

325
00:13:52.817 --> 00:13:55.602
Patrol responded to an incident
there a couple hours ago.

326
00:13:57.592 --> 00:13:59.866
There was a brief shootout
before the gunman fled.

327
00:13:59.867 --> 00:14:02.391
Motel owner reported a man
and a boy at the scene.

328
00:14:02.392 --> 00:14:03.870
They match the descriptions
of Liam and Micah.

329
00:14:03.871 --> 00:14:05.524
All right. let's get
the motel owner in here.

330
00:14:05.525 --> 00:14:07.527
- find out more about what he saw.
- Let's go.

331
00:14:10.967 --> 00:14:12.923
- Just take a seat.
- Thanks.

332
00:14:12.924 --> 00:14:15.491
Look. I told the cops everything I know.

333
00:14:15.492 --> 00:14:16.883
Three times over.

334
00:14:16.884 --> 00:14:18.885
I'm sure I've got nothing new for you.

335
00:14:18.886 --> 00:14:22.106
You said in your statement there
was a man and a boy at your motel.

336
00:14:22.107 --> 00:14:24.292
- Is this them?
- Yeah.

337
00:14:24.293 --> 00:14:26.452
They checked in about a quarter to 3:00.

338
00:14:26.453 --> 00:14:28.373
The man mention anything about
where they were coming from.

339
00:14:28.374 --> 00:14:30.157
or where they might be headed?

340
00:14:30.158 --> 00:14:33.683
I'm open 24 hours.
I charge 50 bucks a night.

341
00:14:33.684 --> 00:14:35.902
It's not a place where
you ask many questions.

342
00:14:35.903 --> 00:14:37.338
What about their interaction?

343
00:14:37.339 --> 00:14:39.384
Anything odd or distinct you recall?

344
00:14:39.385 --> 00:14:40.820
How so?

345
00:14:40.821 --> 00:14:42.474
Did the little boy have
any marks on him?

346
00:14:42.475 --> 00:14:43.823
Did he seem scared of the man?

347
00:14:43.824 --> 00:14:45.085
No.

348
00:14:45.086 --> 00:14:47.044
It just seemed like
your basic father-son.

349
00:14:47.045 --> 00:14:49.089
Yeah. except the man
isn't the boy's father.

350
00:14:49.090 --> 00:14:50.352
He kidnapped him.

351
00:14:53.138 --> 00:14:54.551
I never would have guessed.

352
00:14:54.552 --> 00:14:57.794
That boy seemed so
comfortable with that man.

353
00:14:57.795 --> 00:15:00.579
But. uh. he was terrified as hell

354
00:15:00.580 --> 00:15:02.407
when the two shooters showed up
and went after them.

355
00:15:02.408 --> 00:15:04.670
Hold on. What do you mean
"went after them"?

356
00:15:04.671 --> 00:15:07.456
I thought the sons of bitches
had come to rob me.

357
00:15:07.457 --> 00:15:09.032
Wouldn't have been the first time.

358
00:15:09.033 --> 00:15:11.295
But no demand for money. Nothing.

359
00:15:11.296 --> 00:15:13.993
Then they saw the man
and the boy in the hallway.

360
00:15:13.994 --> 00:15:16.550
and it was like they'd come for them.

361
00:15:17.428 --> 00:15:19.467
Your motel have security cameras?

362
00:15:21.262 --> 00:15:23.046
This the only camera this place has?

363
00:15:23.047 --> 00:15:24.633
I think there's another one.

364
00:15:27.007 --> 00:15:29.401
All right. There's Liam and Micah.

365
00:15:33.318 --> 00:15:36.530
The shooters are targeting them.
The motel clerk was right.

366
00:15:37.737 --> 00:15:39.932
This isn't about you. old man!

367
00:15:39.933 --> 00:15:41.673
We just want the kid!

368
00:15:41.674 --> 00:15:44.074
These guys aren't after the kidnapper.
They're after the boy.

369
00:15:46.741 --> 00:15:48.493
Liam's protecting Micah from these guys.

370
00:15:48.724 --> 00:15:50.377
Then who the hell are they?

371
00:15:50.378 --> 00:15:52.846
And what could they possibly
want with an innocent child?

372
00:15:55.091 --> 00:15:57.099
Can't make out any patches or insignia.

373
00:15:57.100 --> 00:15:58.847
but judging by the bikes
and their tactics.

374
00:15:58.849 --> 00:16:01.677
my guess is our motel perps
are club affiliated.

375
00:16:01.679 --> 00:16:03.723
Which only muddies the water more.

376
00:16:03.724 --> 00:16:06.796
Why would a biker club
be chasing a little boy?

377
00:16:06.798 --> 00:16:08.641
Hey. boss. we got a
BOLO out on the car

378
00:16:08.642 --> 00:16:10.469
that Liam and Micah left the motel in.

379
00:16:10.470 --> 00:16:12.122
Amber Alert's out as well.

380
00:16:12.123 --> 00:16:13.210
All right. copy that.

381
00:16:13.211 --> 00:16:14.516
This is Detective Ramona Quinn

382
00:16:14.517 --> 00:16:15.996
from the sheriff's
department in Palmdale.

383
00:16:15.997 --> 00:16:17.693
She heard about the shootings
at the Hillwinds Inn.

384
00:16:17.694 --> 00:16:19.335
She thinks she can help us
fill in the blanks.

385
00:16:19.337 --> 00:16:21.152
- Nice to meet you.
- Your shooters belong to

386
00:16:21.154 --> 00:16:23.591
a motorcycle club by the name
of Palmdale Pagans.

387
00:16:23.592 --> 00:16:25.593
They're heavy in the meth trade
and prostitution.

388
00:16:25.594 --> 00:16:27.725
I've been building a case
against them for a while.

389
00:16:27.726 --> 00:16:29.466
but nothing concrete enough to indict.

390
00:16:29.468 --> 00:16:31.766
You got any idea why they would
go after an eight-year-old kid?

391
00:16:31.768 --> 00:16:33.682
Your guess is as good
as mine on that one.

392
00:16:33.684 --> 00:16:36.295
but maybe the why
doesn't matter right now.

393
00:16:36.296 --> 00:16:37.861
The fact remains. they want that boy.

394
00:16:37.862 --> 00:16:40.603
All right. what do you suggest
is the better question?

395
00:16:40.604 --> 00:16:43.389
Where? If Liam Dunn is protecting Micah.

396
00:16:43.390 --> 00:16:45.011
where would he take the boy?

397
00:16:45.013 --> 00:16:46.563
That's the better question.

398
00:16:46.564 --> 00:16:48.842
All right. Liam likely
wants to get Micah someplace safe.

399
00:16:48.843 --> 00:16:50.234
somewhere the Pagans can't find him.

400
00:16:50.235 --> 00:16:51.584
So let's dig into him more.

401
00:16:51.585 --> 00:16:53.194
Family. close friends.
people he can trust.

402
00:16:53.195 --> 00:16:55.545
- People in and around L.A.
- On it.

403
00:17:00.855 --> 00:17:03.290
Abby. we need to know if there's
someone you owe money to.

404
00:17:03.291 --> 00:17:05.294
Someone who would be
very determined to get it back.

405
00:17:05.295 --> 00:17:06.555
Money?

406
00:17:06.556 --> 00:17:09.361
Uh. no. I-I-I don't think so.

407
00:17:10.100 --> 00:17:11.907
I-I mean. the only thing
I can think is that I-I...

408
00:17:11.908 --> 00:17:13.387
My boss gave me an advance

409
00:17:13.388 --> 00:17:15.796
on-on my paycheck. I've got to
pay him back for that.

410
00:17:15.797 --> 00:17:17.261
That's not what we mean and you know it.

411
00:17:17.262 --> 00:17:18.741
We're talking about drug dealers.

412
00:17:18.742 --> 00:17:20.439
Are you in debt to drug dealers?

413
00:17:20.440 --> 00:17:23.529
I already told you
that I am not using anymore.

414
00:17:23.530 --> 00:17:26.227
And besides. what does this
have to do with Micah?

415
00:17:26.228 --> 00:17:28.011
I mean. you guys are in here

416
00:17:28.012 --> 00:17:29.926
asking me about my money situation

417
00:17:29.927 --> 00:17:31.232
when my baby's out there.

418
00:17:31.233 --> 00:17:33.364
with some ex-con doing
God knows what to him.

419
00:17:33.365 --> 00:17:35.758
I mean. what is wrong with you people?!

420
00:17:35.759 --> 00:17:36.959
Sit down!

421
00:17:37.419 --> 00:17:38.933
Sit down.

422
00:17:39.815 --> 00:17:41.421
Abby...

423
00:17:41.422 --> 00:17:43.125
Please. sit down.

424
00:17:43.593 --> 00:17:47.031
We want to show you another video.
and I need you to sit.

425
00:17:55.736 --> 00:17:57.301
This isn't about you. old man!

426
00:17:57.302 --> 00:17:58.564
- When was this taken?
- We just want the kid!

427
00:17:58.565 --> 00:18:00.043
That was this morning.

428
00:18:00.044 --> 00:18:01.523
Those gunmen are bikers.

429
00:18:01.524 --> 00:18:03.178
most likely in the drug business.

430
00:18:03.625 --> 00:18:05.745
And the only reason we can think that

431
00:18:05.746 --> 00:18:08.856
they'd want to take Micah is
that they want something from you.

432
00:18:08.857 --> 00:18:09.863
Right.

433
00:18:09.864 --> 00:18:14.504
So. I'm going to ask again.
and it would be really helpful

434
00:18:14.505 --> 00:18:16.593
if you were honest.

435
00:18:16.594 --> 00:18:18.458
Do you owe these guys money?

436
00:18:19.037 --> 00:18:22.039
I have never seen
these people in my life.

437
00:18:22.040 --> 00:18:23.823
Well. then what could they
possibly want with Micah?

438
00:18:23.824 --> 00:18:26.567
- I don't know. I swear.
- You know. the more I think about this.

439
00:18:26.568 --> 00:18:28.654
the more I just can't shake the feeling

440
00:18:28.655 --> 00:18:30.986
that Micah's disappearance has
to do with your drug problem.

441
00:18:30.987 --> 00:18:32.963
Fine. maybe a year ago. but not anymore.

442
00:18:32.964 --> 00:18:35.649
I am doing everything I can
to take care of Micah

443
00:18:35.650 --> 00:18:37.597
- and to give him a better life!
- Oh. come on.

444
00:18:37.598 --> 00:18:39.010
All right. Let's-let's go back.

445
00:18:39.011 --> 00:18:40.709
The truth is. Abby. Micah is missing

446
00:18:40.710 --> 00:18:42.277
because of your bad choices.

447
00:18:42.278 --> 00:18:44.453
and now he just might turn up
dead because of your lies.

448
00:18:44.454 --> 00:18:47.935
Officer Street... take a walk.

449
00:18:47.936 --> 00:18:49.136
Now.

450
00:18:59.730 --> 00:19:02.308
You know. I've seen a lot
of people sit in that chair.

451
00:19:03.292 --> 00:19:05.561
And over the years. I've gotten
pretty good at knowing

452
00:19:05.562 --> 00:19:06.955
when they're lying to me.

453
00:19:09.833 --> 00:19:12.047
I believe you're telling me the truth.

454
00:19:14.963 --> 00:19:18.445
Now. is there anything that...
that Micah talks to you about?

455
00:19:18.748 --> 00:19:21.969
You know. um. something
that he might be into lately?

456
00:19:24.277 --> 00:19:26.452
The last couple weeks. he's been...

457
00:19:26.453 --> 00:19:28.750
he's been begging me for a skateboard.

458
00:19:29.325 --> 00:19:32.424
I mean. he needs new shoes.
but he just...

459
00:19:33.547 --> 00:19:35.592
He can't stop talking
about a skateboard.

460
00:19:36.042 --> 00:19:38.203
You know. when he rides the bus.

461
00:19:38.204 --> 00:19:40.422
he sees these skaters
at this old warehouse

462
00:19:40.423 --> 00:19:42.250
next to the shelter.

463
00:19:43.557 --> 00:19:45.733
He loves watching them.

464
00:19:53.973 --> 00:19:55.304
All right.

465
00:19:55.306 --> 00:19:58.701
I'm gonna give you a chance
to talk to me as your friend

466
00:19:58.702 --> 00:20:00.960
and convince me that
your behavior in there was

467
00:20:00.962 --> 00:20:03.742
- just a momentary lack of judgment.
- Last I checked.

468
00:20:03.744 --> 00:20:06.448
there's only one victim here.
and it's Micah.

469
00:20:06.449 --> 00:20:07.841
Abby may have you fooled.

470
00:20:07.842 --> 00:20:09.712
but she sure as hell
doesn't have me fooled.

471
00:20:09.713 --> 00:20:11.236
But she does have you fooled.

472
00:20:11.237 --> 00:20:13.020
She's got you thinking
she's your mother.

473
00:20:13.021 --> 00:20:15.718
Street. whether you believe it or not.

474
00:20:15.719 --> 00:20:17.778
that woman in there is doing everything

475
00:20:17.779 --> 00:20:19.549
she can to change
the course of her life.

476
00:20:19.819 --> 00:20:21.525
For herself and her son.

477
00:20:25.314 --> 00:20:26.751
We done here?

478
00:20:27.915 --> 00:20:29.220
Okay.

479
00:20:29.222 --> 00:20:31.137
Now I'm gonna talk to you
as your sergeant.

480
00:20:32.301 --> 00:20:34.563
Micah's case has
brought out a side of you

481
00:20:34.564 --> 00:20:36.783
that is fogging your judgment.
I am removing you from it.

482
00:20:36.784 --> 00:20:38.306
Wh-What?

483
00:20:38.307 --> 00:20:39.742
You're benching me? Deacon...

484
00:20:39.743 --> 00:20:41.832
Now we're done here.

485
00:20:46.527 --> 00:20:48.094
What was that about?

486
00:20:49.483 --> 00:20:51.608
I'm benched from Micah's case.

487
00:20:52.047 --> 00:20:53.358
What?

488
00:20:53.744 --> 00:20:55.920
Deacon thinks that
my history with my mom

489
00:20:55.921 --> 00:20:57.835
is messing with my head. but it's not.

490
00:20:57.836 --> 00:20:59.619
It's actually what's giving me clarity.

491
00:20:59.620 --> 00:21:02.329
Abby's a drug addict.
drug dealers want her son.

492
00:21:02.330 --> 00:21:03.797
It's not that hard to connect the dots.

493
00:21:03.798 --> 00:21:06.234
- Maybe.
- Oh. what. you agree with Deac?

494
00:21:06.235 --> 00:21:08.846
- Finding Micah is the priority.
- You don't think I know that?

495
00:21:08.847 --> 00:21:11.110
Let me finish.
We all want to find that kid.

496
00:21:11.608 --> 00:21:13.502
But no one wants that more than Abby.

497
00:21:13.503 --> 00:21:15.156
Only a parent would go to the extremes

498
00:21:15.157 --> 00:21:16.942
that she went to to get him back.

499
00:21:18.150 --> 00:21:19.770
People can change for the better.

500
00:21:20.025 --> 00:21:22.817
It's easy to forget that in
our line of work. but they can.

501
00:21:23.108 --> 00:21:24.513
I know that wasn't true of your mom.

502
00:21:24.514 --> 00:21:27.299
but it is true of you. Street.

503
00:21:27.300 --> 00:21:28.997
You're living proof of that.

504
00:21:35.569 --> 00:21:37.962
Commander. we did a deep dive
on Liam Dunn's past.

505
00:21:37.963 --> 00:21:40.181
You find anything that'd shed
a little more light

506
00:21:40.182 --> 00:21:41.530
- on what we're dealing with here?
- Maybe.

507
00:21:41.531 --> 00:21:43.315
Liam had a son. Seven years ago.

508
00:21:43.316 --> 00:21:45.012
the kid got caught in the crossfire

509
00:21:45.013 --> 00:21:47.580
of a convenience store
holdup. He was killed.

510
00:21:47.581 --> 00:21:49.147
He was ten years old at the time.

511
00:21:49.148 --> 00:21:51.845
Seems to be what launched
the spiral of Liam's life.

512
00:21:51.846 --> 00:21:53.542
Lost his job. his marriage.

513
00:21:53.543 --> 00:21:55.327
started getting in trouble with the law.

514
00:21:55.328 --> 00:21:57.438
That explains why
he was so paternal with Micah.

515
00:21:57.439 --> 00:21:59.823
Also explains why
Liam didn't go to the cops.

516
00:21:59.824 --> 00:22:01.246
The day that his son was killed.

517
00:22:01.247 --> 00:22:03.944
first officers on the scene
pegged Liam as the shooter.

518
00:22:03.945 --> 00:22:05.424
They took him down.
roughed him up pretty bad.

519
00:22:05.425 --> 00:22:08.254
All while his son was
bleeding out a few feet away.

520
00:22:08.733 --> 00:22:10.080
Whew. Well. that'd
definitely make someone

521
00:22:10.081 --> 00:22:11.560
not trust a badge after that.

522
00:22:11.561 --> 00:22:13.954
Anything in Liam's backstory

523
00:22:13.955 --> 00:22:17.113
about other family.
someone he might've turned to?

524
00:22:17.114 --> 00:22:18.723
None. Just the wife.

525
00:22:18.724 --> 00:22:20.753
Before their son's death.
they lived in Pasadena.

526
00:22:20.754 --> 00:22:22.437
That's the ex-wife's last known address.

527
00:22:22.438 --> 00:22:23.771
Has there been any contact between them?

528
00:22:23.772 --> 00:22:26.105
No evidence of it.
Call logs from Corcoran indicate

529
00:22:26.106 --> 00:22:28.254
no communication between them
during the five years

530
00:22:28.255 --> 00:22:29.951
- he was locked up.
- All right. just the same.

531
00:22:29.952 --> 00:22:31.779
let's get Pasadena P.D.
to get a unit over to

532
00:22:31.780 --> 00:22:33.955
the ex-wife's place.
keep an eye out in case

533
00:22:33.956 --> 00:22:35.349
Liam or Micah shows up.

534
00:22:36.176 --> 00:22:38.134
They got to be getting
pretty desperate by now.

535
00:22:38.135 --> 00:22:40.833
- Might be enough to drive them her way.
- Yeah.

536
00:22:42.922 --> 00:22:44.402
What are you doing?

537
00:22:44.776 --> 00:22:46.149
Whose car is this?

538
00:22:46.150 --> 00:22:48.362
It belongs to a friend.

539
00:22:48.608 --> 00:22:50.103
A friend?

540
00:22:51.800 --> 00:22:54.107
He didn't give you the keys?

541
00:23:02.289 --> 00:23:03.811
Come on. Micah.

542
00:23:03.812 --> 00:23:05.161
Get in. We got to go.

543
00:23:05.162 --> 00:23:07.317
This isn't your friend's car. huh?

544
00:23:12.473 --> 00:23:13.909
No.

545
00:23:14.736 --> 00:23:16.998
Should we... go to the police now or...?

546
00:23:16.999 --> 00:23:18.653
No. we can't.

547
00:23:20.002 --> 00:23:21.202
I've...

548
00:23:23.397 --> 00:23:24.833
Look...

549
00:23:25.834 --> 00:23:28.446
I've done some things in my life.

550
00:23:28.817 --> 00:23:31.622
Things that make the police not like me

551
00:23:31.623 --> 00:23:33.320
or want to help me.

552
00:23:34.278 --> 00:23:38.543
And if we go to them.
then I can't help you.

553
00:23:39.275 --> 00:23:40.893
Does that make sense?

554
00:23:41.275 --> 00:23:42.475
No.

555
00:23:42.817 --> 00:23:44.025
You're a good guy.

556
00:23:44.026 --> 00:23:46.317
Don't the police help the good guys?

557
00:23:49.336 --> 00:23:50.772
Micah...

558
00:23:52.600 --> 00:23:55.515
I'm gonna take you to a police station

559
00:23:55.516 --> 00:23:56.908
- and drop you off.
- No...

560
00:23:56.909 --> 00:23:58.388
You promised you'd stay with me.

561
00:23:58.389 --> 00:24:00.694
They can help you better than I can.

562
00:24:00.695 --> 00:24:03.610
You said a man who breaks
promises is a man of bad character.

563
00:24:03.611 --> 00:24:05.222
Don't leave me.

564
00:24:06.432 --> 00:24:07.900
Please.

565
00:24:10.531 --> 00:24:13.186
All right. I won't. kiddo.

566
00:24:14.187 --> 00:24:16.346
I'm gonna take you
to a safe place. okay?

567
00:24:16.348 --> 00:24:17.537
Okay.

568
00:24:17.539 --> 00:24:19.470
Get in the car. Come on.

569
00:24:25.564 --> 00:24:28.138
Deac and I will see what
we can get from Liam's ex-wife.

570
00:24:28.140 --> 00:24:30.209
The two of you. take a crack
at the wounded biker.

571
00:24:30.210 --> 00:24:32.172
See if he'll give up anything
on where to find his pals.

572
00:24:32.173 --> 00:24:33.373
Okay.

573
00:24:40.993 --> 00:24:42.175
Ms. Reese.

574
00:24:42.176 --> 00:24:44.761
I'm Sergeant Harrelson.
this is Sergeant Kay.

575
00:24:45.580 --> 00:24:47.781
I already spoke with the other cops.

576
00:24:47.782 --> 00:24:48.869
We know.

577
00:24:48.870 --> 00:24:51.219
We're just worried about the little boy

578
00:24:51.220 --> 00:24:52.830
that's with your ex-husband.

579
00:24:53.178 --> 00:24:55.267
We're afraid they're
running out of time.

580
00:24:55.268 --> 00:24:58.094
Have you seen the boy? Was he with Liam?

581
00:24:59.707 --> 00:25:02.622
I thought. at first. I was dreaming.

582
00:25:02.623 --> 00:25:05.103
He looked so much like our son.

583
00:25:05.104 --> 00:25:06.761
The son you lost.

584
00:25:07.678 --> 00:25:09.151
What was your boy's name?

585
00:25:09.809 --> 00:25:11.053
Clayton.

586
00:25:12.227 --> 00:25:13.489
We called him Clay.

587
00:25:14.094 --> 00:25:16.418
I was in the yard. just gardening.

588
00:25:16.419 --> 00:25:18.203
I saw them walking toward me.

589
00:25:18.204 --> 00:25:22.468
For a moment. I...
I don't know. it just...

590
00:25:22.469 --> 00:25:26.429
felt like the last time I saw Clay.

591
00:25:27.778 --> 00:25:33.000
Except this time.
he and Liam were coming home...

592
00:25:33.001 --> 00:25:34.894
unhurt. safe.

593
00:25:34.895 --> 00:25:37.918
Ms. Reese. we're trying to save

594
00:25:37.919 --> 00:25:40.530
another mother from going
through what you had to endure.

595
00:25:42.228 --> 00:25:45.318
When you saw Liam.
what did he talk about?

596
00:25:46.331 --> 00:25:48.233
He said there were

597
00:25:48.234 --> 00:25:51.136
bad people who wanted to harm the boy.

598
00:25:51.969 --> 00:25:53.978
He asked if he could stay with me.

599
00:25:54.678 --> 00:25:56.807
He thought he would be safe there.

600
00:25:57.057 --> 00:25:58.257
He was wrong.

601
00:25:58.678 --> 00:26:00.680
We heard motorcycles.

602
00:26:00.681 --> 00:26:05.032
There were four of them. all with guns.

603
00:26:05.033 --> 00:26:07.077
They just started shooting.

604
00:26:07.078 --> 00:26:10.473
I urged Liam to go.
for the child's sake.

605
00:26:11.219 --> 00:26:13.780
Two of the bikers went after them.

606
00:26:13.781 --> 00:26:15.511
Two stayed behind.

607
00:26:16.553 --> 00:26:18.873
wanting me to tell them
where Liam had gone.

608
00:26:19.362 --> 00:26:20.561
And did you?

609
00:26:20.562 --> 00:26:23.136
I couldn't. I don't know
where Liam went.

610
00:26:25.671 --> 00:26:27.890
Protecting that child.

611
00:26:30.026 --> 00:26:33.116
I think it's his way of protecting Clay.

612
00:26:35.063 --> 00:26:37.064
I won't fault him for that.

613
00:26:37.065 --> 00:26:38.718
We understand.

614
00:26:38.719 --> 00:26:42.079
Do you recall Micah saying
anything. anything at all?

615
00:26:42.080 --> 00:26:44.932
Besides wanting his mother?

616
00:26:45.900 --> 00:26:49.382
He mentioned a place she takes him.

617
00:26:49.652 --> 00:26:51.510
called it "a hiding place."

618
00:26:51.511 --> 00:26:53.994
Said he and Liam should go there.

619
00:26:53.995 --> 00:26:56.258
He's just a child. so...

620
00:27:02.482 --> 00:27:05.048
- You have any luck with him?
- Hardly.

621
00:27:05.049 --> 00:27:06.572
Told you he's not much of a talker.

622
00:27:06.573 --> 00:27:08.008
Too bad the bullet that hit him wasn't

623
00:27:08.009 --> 00:27:09.562
a couple inches to the left.
you know what I mean?

624
00:27:09.563 --> 00:27:10.881
Yeah.

625
00:27:11.219 --> 00:27:13.666
Come on. did you really expect
that guy to open up to us?

626
00:27:13.667 --> 00:27:16.408
Nah. but there's still something
that's bugging me.

627
00:27:16.409 --> 00:27:18.888
Our intel on Liam's ex-wife.

628
00:27:18.889 --> 00:27:20.455
Okay. we had to dig deep
to make the link

629
00:27:20.456 --> 00:27:22.327
to the house in Pasadena.

630
00:27:22.328 --> 00:27:24.503
How the hell'd the Pagans
get there so fast?

631
00:27:24.504 --> 00:27:27.157
They could've run a bootleg
background check on Liam.

632
00:27:27.158 --> 00:27:29.247
Yeah. but he was working
at the shelter under an alias.

633
00:27:29.248 --> 00:27:31.164
They didn't even know his real name.

634
00:27:31.165 --> 00:27:33.472
And there's something else.
Larry Callahan.

635
00:27:33.473 --> 00:27:35.383
the murder victim from
the warehouse last night.

636
00:27:35.384 --> 00:27:37.709
- Yeah. what about him?
- The dude was an alcoholic

637
00:27:37.710 --> 00:27:39.341
with no money.

638
00:27:39.342 --> 00:27:42.085
and somehow he was able to get his
criminal record expunged.

639
00:27:42.086 --> 00:27:43.652
That takes connections.

640
00:27:43.653 --> 00:27:45.219
Think he knew someone
in law enforcement?

641
00:27:45.220 --> 00:27:46.438
Like. working as a CI?

642
00:27:46.439 --> 00:27:49.268
That would explain why the
Pagans put a bullet in his head.

643
00:27:50.830 --> 00:27:53.048
I know a guy from my
sheriff's department days.

644
00:27:53.049 --> 00:27:54.833
used to work patrol in Palmdale.

645
00:27:54.834 --> 00:27:56.705
I'll call him. see if
he knows anything.

646
00:27:59.391 --> 00:28:00.926
Any news about Micah?

647
00:28:00.927 --> 00:28:03.451
He's alive. but we haven't found him.

648
00:28:03.453 --> 00:28:04.724
We need your help.

649
00:28:04.726 --> 00:28:06.029
Help?

650
00:28:06.031 --> 00:28:08.324
Can you tell us more about
your routine with Micah?

651
00:28:08.325 --> 00:28:10.196
Any places he felt particularly safe.

652
00:28:10.197 --> 00:28:13.025
- Why? Wh-What's going on?
- Micah may have gone

653
00:28:13.026 --> 00:28:14.983
somewhere he calls his hiding place.

654
00:28:14.984 --> 00:28:16.681
Does that make any sense?

655
00:28:16.682 --> 00:28:18.160
The caves.

656
00:28:18.161 --> 00:28:19.361
Up at Griffith Park.

657
00:28:19.363 --> 00:28:21.629
- Off the Rock Canyon Trail.
- Yeah.

658
00:28:21.630 --> 00:28:23.949
Sometimes when I.
when I couldn't afford a motel

659
00:28:23.950 --> 00:28:27.344
or when the shelters were too full.
I-I'd sneak him in there.

660
00:28:27.769 --> 00:28:30.704
Then we'd pretend we were
on a deserted island.

661
00:28:30.705 --> 00:28:32.284
You know. like. I'd light a candle

662
00:28:32.285 --> 00:28:33.741
and we'd pretend it was a fire.

663
00:28:33.742 --> 00:28:36.526
Or I'd get fish fillet sandwiches.

664
00:28:36.527 --> 00:28:38.660
and pretend we caught a fish.

665
00:28:39.705 --> 00:28:42.055
Yeah. he-he loved it.

666
00:28:46.009 --> 00:28:47.887
Hey. look. Please find him.

667
00:28:48.606 --> 00:28:49.806
We're working on it.

668
00:28:50.284 --> 00:28:52.398
We need to get to Griffith Park
before the Pagans do.

669
00:28:52.399 --> 00:28:54.618
The rest of 20-Squad's
still out in Pasadena.

670
00:28:54.619 --> 00:28:57.621
- I can get there faster.
- Without your squad? Hell no.

671
00:28:57.622 --> 00:29:00.058
- Then send the both of us.
- Benched is benched. Street.

672
00:29:00.059 --> 00:29:01.973
I get that. but what
other option do we have?

673
00:29:01.974 --> 00:29:03.801
Rest of the team's too far away.

674
00:29:03.802 --> 00:29:05.978
I can provide backup.

675
00:29:06.478 --> 00:29:07.674
Street's right.

676
00:29:07.675 --> 00:29:08.893
If the Pagans show up.

677
00:29:08.894 --> 00:29:10.721
I'll know exactly what to say to them

678
00:29:10.722 --> 00:29:13.072
before the bastards even think
about pulling the trigger.

679
00:29:13.569 --> 00:29:15.061
What do you think. Commander?

680
00:29:17.511 --> 00:29:22.255
Detective. you better have
my officers' six at all times.

681
00:29:23.691 --> 00:29:25.041
Let's roll.

682
00:29:30.916 --> 00:29:32.612
Are you okay?

683
00:29:32.613 --> 00:29:34.180
Yeah.

684
00:29:35.548 --> 00:29:37.103
Yeah. Let's go.

685
00:29:42.058 --> 00:29:45.269
- Yeah. okay.
- Are you okay?

686
00:29:49.065 --> 00:29:51.240
I just need a minute.

687
00:29:51.241 --> 00:29:53.329
No. No. no. no. It's cold.

688
00:29:53.330 --> 00:29:55.985
- You keep that on.
- I'm not cold. okay?

689
00:29:58.644 --> 00:30:01.033
I once knew a little boy...

690
00:30:01.310 --> 00:30:04.791
kind and brave like you.

691
00:30:06.449 --> 00:30:08.320
I miss him...

692
00:30:09.661 --> 00:30:10.861
so much.

693
00:30:11.592 --> 00:30:13.500
What was his name?

694
00:30:16.088 --> 00:30:18.220
Wake up. please.

695
00:30:18.222 --> 00:30:20.485
Please. wake up!

696
00:30:25.740 --> 00:30:27.132
All right. listen up.

697
00:30:27.133 --> 00:30:29.004
I talked to Hicks.
Tan and Detective Quinn

698
00:30:29.005 --> 00:30:30.309
already rolled out to Griffith Park.

699
00:30:30.310 --> 00:30:31.789
The sooner we get there. the better.

700
00:30:31.790 --> 00:30:33.182
Now. there is no telling

701
00:30:33.183 --> 00:30:34.661
how many Pagans
might show up to the party.

702
00:30:34.662 --> 00:30:36.198
Okay. we should just stick to
the side streets.

703
00:30:36.199 --> 00:30:37.388
The 110's a nightmare.

704
00:30:37.389 --> 00:30:39.898
Appreciate you calling me back.
I got to run. Thanks.

705
00:30:39.899 --> 00:30:41.973
- What's up?
- Problem's bigger than we think.

706
00:30:41.974 --> 00:30:44.019
Hondo. I just heard back
from a friend of mine.

707
00:30:44.020 --> 00:30:45.498
used to work Palmdale.

708
00:30:45.499 --> 00:30:47.676
Larry Callahan. guy the Pagans
killed last night?

709
00:30:47.677 --> 00:30:50.025
Good chance
Detective Quinn was in on that.

710
00:30:50.026 --> 00:30:51.722
Wait a minute. what're you saying?

711
00:30:51.723 --> 00:30:53.332
Internal Affairs
up in Palmdale's been running

712
00:30:53.333 --> 00:30:55.204
an investigation into
crooked cops suspected of

713
00:30:55.205 --> 00:30:57.423
taking protection money
from the meth trade.

714
00:30:57.424 --> 00:30:59.382
The investigation had a CI.

715
00:30:59.383 --> 00:31:00.862
It was Larry Callahan.

716
00:31:02.586 --> 00:31:04.474
Hondo. if Quinn is one of
those dirty cops.

717
00:31:04.475 --> 00:31:06.389
that would explain why
she showed up on our doorstep

718
00:31:06.390 --> 00:31:07.912
right after the shootout at the motel.

719
00:31:07.913 --> 00:31:10.480
It also explains how the Pagans
got to the Pasadena house so fast.

720
00:31:10.481 --> 00:31:11.916
I mean.
I know it's just a theory. but...

721
00:31:11.917 --> 00:31:13.701
But Tan's alone with her right now.

722
00:31:22.710 --> 00:31:24.015
Deac. you guys close?

723
00:31:24.016 --> 00:31:25.736
Hey. Tan. listen.
we need you to get away...

724
00:31:27.759 --> 00:31:29.294
I can't hear you. Deac?

725
00:31:30.378 --> 00:31:32.086
Afraid you're out of luck.

726
00:31:33.417 --> 00:31:35.375
No signal up here.

727
00:31:39.945 --> 00:31:42.034
Please. wake up!

728
00:31:43.775 --> 00:31:45.123
Micah?

729
00:31:45.124 --> 00:31:46.255
Hey.

730
00:31:46.256 --> 00:31:48.822
I think he's dead...

731
00:31:48.823 --> 00:31:50.085
He's hanging on.

732
00:31:50.086 --> 00:31:51.434
We're gonna get him some help. okay?

733
00:31:51.435 --> 00:31:53.176
Okay. Okay. Okay.

734
00:31:54.133 --> 00:31:55.525
That's the bad lady! She was there!

735
00:31:55.526 --> 00:31:56.961
Move. move. Move. move!

736
00:31:56.962 --> 00:31:58.289
Get down. get down!

737
00:32:03.076 --> 00:32:04.328
Stay low.

738
00:32:16.972 --> 00:32:18.930
The math is simple.

739
00:32:19.417 --> 00:32:21.019
There's three of us.

740
00:32:21.605 --> 00:32:24.995
then there's you with a dead
ex-con and an eight-year-old.

741
00:32:25.459 --> 00:32:26.939
Hand over the kid.

742
00:32:27.443 --> 00:32:29.430
The warehouse last night...

743
00:32:29.431 --> 00:32:31.808
You had Larry Callahan killed!

744
00:32:31.809 --> 00:32:34.114
The kid has nothing to do
with this mess.

745
00:32:34.115 --> 00:32:36.177
It's not my fault he's in this position.

746
00:32:36.178 --> 00:32:39.703
What mother lets her child
wander off in the middle of the night?

747
00:32:46.333 --> 00:32:48.083
Stay down. Stay down.

748
00:32:50.117 --> 00:32:51.735
Toss your gun.

749
00:32:51.736 --> 00:32:53.476
and turn over the kid.

750
00:32:53.976 --> 00:32:55.782
We don't have to make this messy.

751
00:32:55.783 --> 00:32:57.611
We both know that's not happening.

752
00:33:06.476 --> 00:33:08.012
We got to move. Micah.

753
00:33:08.013 --> 00:33:09.226
Go. Come on.

754
00:33:19.046 --> 00:33:20.246
Move!

755
00:33:21.892 --> 00:33:23.593
Right here.

756
00:33:30.351 --> 00:33:32.559
All right. get down. get down. get down.

757
00:33:33.429 --> 00:33:34.995
This is where your mom took you?

758
00:33:34.996 --> 00:33:36.309
Yeah.

759
00:33:36.310 --> 00:33:38.303
It's our hiding spot.

760
00:33:38.304 --> 00:33:39.870
Your mom said you come here
and play desert island.

761
00:33:39.871 --> 00:33:41.698
Said you have a lot of fun doing that.

762
00:33:44.226 --> 00:33:45.484
It's all my fault.

763
00:33:45.485 --> 00:33:47.791
Should've never left the shelter.

764
00:33:47.792 --> 00:33:49.749
No. it's not your fault.

765
00:33:49.750 --> 00:33:52.360
You're human. and humans
mess up all the time.

766
00:33:52.361 --> 00:33:54.885
What counts is that we clean it up

767
00:33:54.886 --> 00:33:57.278
and try hard not to make
the same mess again.

768
00:33:57.279 --> 00:33:59.368
- You understand? Okay.
- Yeah.

769
00:34:05.374 --> 00:34:06.766
Come on. Tan.

770
00:34:06.767 --> 00:34:09.247
How long do you really think
you can last?

771
00:34:09.248 --> 00:34:10.902
A lot longer than you think!

772
00:34:12.686 --> 00:34:14.351
LAPD! Guns on the ground.

773
00:34:16.603 --> 00:34:18.934
We got a runner. Powell. with me.

774
00:34:22.101 --> 00:34:23.925
All this and for what. Ramona?

775
00:34:23.926 --> 00:34:25.579
A little extra money?

776
00:34:25.580 --> 00:34:27.800
Isn't it always about the money?

777
00:34:45.879 --> 00:34:47.079
Drop your weapon!

778
00:34:47.309 --> 00:34:48.733
Get on your knees.

779
00:34:48.734 --> 00:34:51.041
- Going hands-on.
- Go.

780
00:35:03.662 --> 00:35:06.276
30-David. suspect in custody.

781
00:35:06.277 --> 00:35:09.711
By the way. Chopper Jack's
a lame-ass nickname.

782
00:35:12.059 --> 00:35:14.194
Don't make this harder on yourself.

783
00:35:15.152 --> 00:35:17.066
- Luca.
- Yeah?

784
00:35:17.067 --> 00:35:19.678
- I climb that. I get a better angle.
- Okay. be careful. boss.

785
00:35:33.170 --> 00:35:35.824
There's no way out of here for you!

786
00:35:47.488 --> 00:35:48.880
Don't you move!

787
00:35:48.881 --> 00:35:51.665
Don't you move.20-David. suspect down.

788
00:35:51.666 --> 00:35:53.711
Code 4 all the way around.

789
00:35:53.712 --> 00:35:54.929
Come on. It's all right.

790
00:35:54.930 --> 00:35:56.665
- You sure?
- Let's go. We're safe.

791
00:35:56.666 --> 00:35:58.673
Deacon. Powell. you got eyes on Liam?

792
00:35:59.003 --> 00:36:00.396
Yeah.

793
00:36:02.066 --> 00:36:03.266
He's dead.

794
00:36:05.245 --> 00:36:06.854
Copy.

795
00:36:06.855 --> 00:36:09.152
I'll call his ex-wife.
and give her the news myself.

796
00:36:17.434 --> 00:36:18.779
Take her to the car.

797
00:36:18.780 --> 00:36:20.739
Yeah. With pleasure.

798
00:36:25.935 --> 00:36:27.048
Hey.

799
00:36:27.049 --> 00:36:28.434
You're safe now.

800
00:36:29.101 --> 00:36:32.098
- Let's get him home.
- Yeah. Come on. Micah.

801
00:36:40.074 --> 00:36:41.578
Come on.

802
00:36:41.579 --> 00:36:42.928
Come with me.

803
00:36:43.392 --> 00:36:45.851
Why? What's going on?

804
00:36:47.791 --> 00:36:49.476
He doesn't need to see you like this.

805
00:36:50.943 --> 00:36:52.162
Who?

806
00:36:53.851 --> 00:36:55.207
Micah?!

807
00:36:55.208 --> 00:36:56.643
- Mommy!
- Oh. my God.

808
00:36:56.644 --> 00:36:59.255
- Mama. Mommy. Mommy!
- Oh. my God.

809
00:36:59.256 --> 00:37:01.605
Oh. my God. I missed you so much.

810
00:37:01.606 --> 00:37:03.184
Let me see you.

811
00:37:04.086 --> 00:37:06.131
- I'm so sorry.
- No. no. I'm sorry.

812
00:37:06.132 --> 00:37:07.959
It's my fault. okay?

813
00:37:07.960 --> 00:37:10.222
Can we. can we leave now?

814
00:37:10.223 --> 00:37:11.397
Um...

815
00:37:11.398 --> 00:37:13.618
I don't know if we can just yet. baby.

816
00:37:14.445 --> 00:37:15.967
We're. um...

817
00:37:15.968 --> 00:37:18.619
we're doing everything we can
to keep you two together.

818
00:37:18.620 --> 00:37:20.494
We just need a little time. okay?

819
00:37:21.726 --> 00:37:23.062
Thank you.

820
00:37:23.476 --> 00:37:24.803
Hey. Micah.

821
00:37:25.309 --> 00:37:26.891
you guys want to spend
some time together?

822
00:37:26.892 --> 00:37:28.762
- We'll get you some food.
- Yeah.

823
00:37:28.763 --> 00:37:30.503
- Yeah?
- Okay. let's do it.

824
00:37:30.504 --> 00:37:32.636
Come on. bud.

825
00:37:32.637 --> 00:37:34.333
Come on. Let's go.

826
00:37:34.334 --> 00:37:35.814
Oh. I missed you so much.

827
00:37:36.767 --> 00:37:38.164
Abby's situation...

828
00:37:39.934 --> 00:37:41.239
You were right.

829
00:37:41.642 --> 00:37:43.328
Just took me a little
while to realize it.

830
00:37:43.892 --> 00:37:45.286
We're good.

831
00:37:45.287 --> 00:37:46.767
Thanks.

832
00:37:56.951 --> 00:37:58.387
Hey.

833
00:38:00.434 --> 00:38:02.043
Hey. baby.

834
00:38:03.638 --> 00:38:04.851
You okay?

835
00:38:07.176 --> 00:38:09.918
No. I'm not.

836
00:38:11.705 --> 00:38:13.141
Talk to me.

837
00:38:16.274 --> 00:38:19.800
I spent the day thinking
about this morning.

838
00:38:21.018 --> 00:38:23.325
And why I want to baptize our daughter.

839
00:38:24.059 --> 00:38:26.023
And I think I figured it out.

840
00:38:27.296 --> 00:38:28.496
Okay.

841
00:38:30.158 --> 00:38:32.552
We almost lost an
eight-year-old boy today.

842
00:38:33.922 --> 00:38:36.533
It's a day I've lived
a hundred times before.

843
00:38:38.732 --> 00:38:40.351
But the difference now?

844
00:38:41.996 --> 00:38:43.726
I'm scared. Nichelle.

845
00:38:44.651 --> 00:38:46.870
Of course. I'm excited.

846
00:38:48.263 --> 00:38:51.092
But I am scared to bring
a child into this world.

847
00:38:53.007 --> 00:38:55.400
I have lived my life protecting people.

848
00:38:56.184 --> 00:38:57.851
protecting children...

849
00:38:59.279 --> 00:39:01.368
but my own child?

850
00:39:03.017 --> 00:39:04.671
I don't know this fear.

851
00:39:08.413 --> 00:39:11.938
I guess a baptism is
my way of giving our kid

852
00:39:11.939 --> 00:39:13.976
an extra layer of protection.

853
00:39:21.272 --> 00:39:22.776
Let's do it.

854
00:39:24.799 --> 00:39:26.148
Really?

855
00:39:27.800 --> 00:39:31.978
Our baby girl is going to
look beautiful in this.

856
00:39:33.267 --> 00:39:34.831
- Baby...
- But...

857
00:39:35.642 --> 00:39:38.095
I pick the church.

858
00:39:39.619 --> 00:39:41.142
Yes. ma'am.

859
00:39:41.925 --> 00:39:43.797
Mm...

860
00:39:47.373 --> 00:39:48.699
Thank you.
